El atributo override sólo se puede utilizar en definiciones de propiedad de clase. You cannot use the override keyword within a function block.

El atributo virtual sólo se puede utilizar en definiciones de propiedad de clase. You cannot use the virtual attribute when you declare a property that does not belong to a class (for example, when you declare a variable within a function block).

Sustitución no compatible. A function marked override must exactly match the parameter and return type declaration of the function it is overriding. It must have the same number of parameters, each of the same type, and declare the same return type. If any of the parameters are optional, that must match as well. Both functions must use the same access specifier (public, private, and so on) or namespace attribute as well.

Sustitución de una función no marcada como override. If a method in a class overrides a method in a base class, you must explicitly declare it by using the override attribute, as this example shows: 
public override function foo():void{};
No se puede redefinir un método final. The method cannot be extended because it is marked as final in the base class.

Las funciones no pueden ser al mismo tiempo static y virtual.
Las funciones no pueden ser al mismo tiempo final y virtual.

No se encontró el tipo o no es una constante en tiempo de compilación: %s. The class used as a type declaration is either unknown or is an expression that could have different values at run time. Check that you are importing the correct class and that its package location has not changed. Also, check that the package that contains the code (not the imported class) is defined correctly (for example, make sure to use proper ActionScript 3.0 package syntax, and not ActionScript 2.0 syntax).

The error can also occur if the class being referenced is not defined in a namespace that is in use or is not defined as public:

public class Foo{}

If you are using Flex™ Builder™ 2 and the class is in a library, make sure to set the class path for the project.

Se desconoce el inicializador de parámetros o no es una constante en tiempo de compilación.
The value used as the default value for the parameter is either undefined or could have different values at run time. Check that the initializer is spelled correctly, and that the initializer value isn't an expression that could result in different possible values at run time.
Asignación no válida a una variable especificada como constante.
No se puede asignar a un valor sin referencia.
El valor devuelto no debe estar definido. You are attempting to use the return statement within a method that has a declared return type void.

Se desconoce el inicializador de constantes o no es una constante en tiempo de compilación.
The value used to initialize the constant is either undefined or could have different values at run time. Check that the initializer is spelled correctly, and that the initializer value isn't an expression that could result in different possible values at run time.
Los tipos de descriptor de acceso deben coincidir.

El tipo devuelto de una definición de establecimiento debe ser unspecified o void. You cannot specify a return value for a setter function. For example, the following is invalid: 
public function set gamma(g:Number):Number;

The following is valid:

public function set gamma(g:Number):void;
La propiedad es de sólo escritura.

La propiedad es de sólo lectura. This property is defined through a getter function, which allows you to retrieve that property's value. There is no setter function defined for this property, however, so it is read-only.

In the following example, line 3 generates an error because there is no setter function defined for xx: 

class D { function get xx() { return 22; } }
var d:D = new D();
d.xx = 44; // error, property is read-only

Error de sintaxis: se esperaba una palabra clave de definición (como function) después del atributo %s, no %s. This error will occur if the author forgets to use the "var" or "function" keyword in a declaration. 
public int z;// should be 'public var z:int;'
This error might also occur when the compiler encounters an unexpected character. For example, the following use of the trace() function is invalid, because of the missing parentheses (the correct syntax is trace("hello")): 
trace "hello"

La posible recursión infinita debida a este archivo incluido: %s. A file that is included in the source being compiled contains other include statements that would cause an infinite loop. For example, the following files. a.as and b.as, generate this error because each file tries to include the other.

File a.as contains the following, which attempts to include the file b.as: 

import foo.bar.baz;
include "b.as"
trace(2);

File b.as contains the following, which attempts to include the file a.as: 

include "a.as"

Se detectó una referencia de tipo circular en %s. A class is trying to extend a superclass. For example, class A cannot extend class B if B inherits from A: 
class a extends b { }
class b extends a { }
El atributo public sólo se puede utilizar dentro de un paquete.
El atributo internal sólo se puede utilizar dentro de un paquete.
Un atributo de espacio de nombres definido por el usuario sólo se puede utilizar en el nivel superior de una definición de clase.

Conversión implícita de un valor con tipo estático %s a un tipo %s posiblemente no relacionado. You are using a value that is not of the expected type and no implicit coercion exists to convert it to the expected type.

Perhaps you are using a supertype where a subtype is expected. For example: 

class A {}
var a:A = new A(); 
class B extends A { function f() }
var b : B = a // error

The last statement generates an error because it attempts to assign an object of type A to a variable of type B.

Similarly, the following defines the foo() function, which takes a parameter of type B. The statement foo(a); generates an error because it attempts to use a parameter of type A: 

function foo(x:B) { }
foo(a);

Also, the following statement generates an error because the returned value for foo2() must be type B: 

function foo2():B { return new A(); }

Acceso a una propiedad %s posiblemente no definida mediante una referencia con tipo estático %s. You are attempting to access a property that does not exist for the specified object. For example, the following code generates this error because an int object does not have a property named assortment: 
var i:int = 44;
var str:String = i.assortment;
This error appears only when the compiler is running in strict mode.

Acceso a una propiedad %s no definida. You are attempting to access an undefined variable. For example, if the variable huh has not been defined, a call to it generates this error: 
huh = 55;
This error can appear only when the compiler is running in strict mode.
Una definición captadora no debe tener parámetros.

El tipo devuelto de una definición captadora no debe ser void.
